Figure Caption: Microstructures SEM of a) ternary Sc33Ti33Zr33 alloy, b) quaternary Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 HEA.
X-ray diffraction pattern of the as cast and annealed at 1000˚C/24h Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 HEA with two marked phases with hexagonal and cubic structures.
TEM-BF image of Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 HEA with marked places of chemical analysis.

TEM observations of Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 HEA, a) BF image of plates with SAED pattern, b) DF at [0001] zone axis, showing regions of α(Sc, Zr) with hexagonal structure in bright contrast, c) BF image with SAED pattern from area between laths, d) DF-TEM along the [001] zone axis, showing bright contrast from cubic structure of β-NbTiZr.
Qualitative EDS chemical analysis of Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 alloy, a) STEM image with place of analysis inside large frame, and corresponding distribution maps of b) Nb-map, c) Sc, c) Ti, e) Zr.
Results of microstructure study of Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 alloy after annealing at 1000˚C for 24h; a) SEM-BSE image with marked points of EDS analysis, b) TEM-BF from interface area between two phases.

Qualitative EDS chemical analysis of Nb25Sc25ti25Zr25 high entropy alloy after annealing at 1000˚C/ 24h; a) STEM image with place of analysis inside large frame; distribution maps of b) Nb, c) Sc, d) Ti and e) Zr.
Compression curves of Nb25Sc25Ti25Zr25 HAE; as cast (solid line) and after annealing at 1000˚C/24h (dashed line).
